## Code quality rules

- Every component must implement `OnDestroy` with `takeUntil(this.destroy$)` for subscriptions
- No `console.log` in production code — use dev-mode-only logging or remove
- No hardcoded strings in templates — use translation keys
- No direct DOM manipulation — use Angular renderer or CSS classes
- Prefer `signal()` / `computed()` for new reactive state (Angular 17+), but don't refactor existing code unless asked
- File names: `kebab-case.component.ts`, `kebab-case.service.ts`, `kebab-case.model.ts`

## Translation key convention

```json
{
  "MODULE_NAME": {
    "TITLE": "...",
    "SUBTITLE": "...",
    "CREATE": "...",
    "EDIT": "...",
    "DELETE": "...",
    "FIELD_NAME": "..."
  }
}
```

Always add keys to BOTH `ar.json` AND `en.json` at the same time.

## SCSS component rules

```scss
/* component.scss */
:host {
  display: block;   /* always declare display */
}

/* Use CSS variables from tokens — never hardcode colors */
.my-element {
  color: var(--text-main);
  background: var(--surface);
  border: 1px solid var(--line);
}

/* Dark mode overrides */
[data-theme='dark'] :host .my-element {
  /* override if needed */
}
```

Component SCSS budget: **warning at 20kb, error at 22kb** (angular.json budget).
